---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Getting Started"
  description="Step-by-step guide to issuing your first TLS certificate with KrakenKey. One-time domain setup, then certificates in 4 minutes."
>
  <div class="section-container guide">
    <div class="section-header section-header--lg">
      <h1 class="section-title section-title--xl">Get started with <span class="text-accent">KrakenKey</span></h1>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        From sign-up to a signed TLS certificate in under 10 minutes. This guide walks through every step.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Prerequisites -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2 class="guide-heading">Before you begin</h2>
      <p class="guide-text">You'll need two things:</p>
      <ul class="prereq-list">
        <li>A domain name you own (e.g. <code>example.com</code>)</li>
        <li>Access to your domain's DNS settings (Cloudflare, Route 53, Namecheap, etc.)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 1 -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <div class="step-marker">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Create an account</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="text-muted">
        Head to <a href="https://app.krakenkey.io" class="link">app.krakenkey.io</a> and click <strong>Sign Up</strong>.
        You'll create an account through our identity provider. Once registered, you're redirected to the dashboard.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 2 -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <div class="step-marker">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Add your domain</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="guide-text">
        In the dashboard, scroll to <strong>Domain Management</strong>, enter your domain, and click <strong>Add Domain</strong>.
      </p>
      <p class="guide-text">
        Or via the API:
      </p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><code set:html={`<span class="code-comment"># Add a domain</span>
curl -X POST https://api.krakenkey.io/domains \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\
  -d '{"hostname": "example.com"}'`} /></pre>
      </div>
      <p class="text-muted">
        The response includes a <code>verificationCode</code> you'll need in the next step.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 3 -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <div class="step-marker">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Add DNS records</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="guide-text guide-text--lg">
        You need two DNS records. The dashboard shows exact values for your domain &mdash; here's what they look like:
      </p>

      <h3 class="guide-subheading">Record 1: TXT &mdash; Ownership verification</h3>
      <p class="guide-text">
        Proves you control the domain. This record must stay in your DNS permanently.
      </p>
      <div class="dns-table-wrap">
        <table class="dns-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Type</th><th>Name</th><th>Value</th><th>TTL</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>TXT</code></td>
              <td><code>@</code></td>
              <td><code>krakenkey-site-verification=abc123...</code></td>
              <td>Auto</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h3 class="guide-subheading guide-subheading--spaced">Record 2: CNAME &mdash; ACME challenge delegation</h3>
      <p class="guide-text">
        Lets KrakenKey respond to Let's Encrypt DNS-01 challenges on your behalf. This is what makes certificate issuance automatic.
      </p>
      <div class="dns-table-wrap">
        <table class="dns-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Type</th><th>Name</th><th>Target</th><th>TTL</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>CNAME</code></td>
              <td><code>_acme-challenge</code></td>
              <td><code>example-com.acme.krakenkey.io</code></td>
              <td>Auto</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="guide-note">
        The CNAME target replaces dots with dashes in your hostname: <code>example.com</code> becomes <code>example-com.acme.krakenkey.io</code>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 4 -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <div class="step-marker">
        <div class="step-number">4</div>
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Verify domain ownership</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="guide-text">
        Wait 1&ndash;5 minutes for DNS propagation, then click <strong>Verify Now</strong> in the dashboard.
        You can check propagation with:
      </p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><code>dig TXT example.com +short</code></pre>
      </div>
      <p class="guide-text">
        Or verify via the API:
      </p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><code>curl -X POST https://api.krakenkey.io/domains/<span class="code-muted">DOMAIN_ID</span>/verify \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN"</code></pre>
      </div>
      <p class="text-muted">
        Once verified, the domain status changes to <strong class="text-accent">Verified</strong> and you can start issuing certificates.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 5 -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <div class="step-marker">
        <div class="step-number">5</div>
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Generate a Certificate Signing Request</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="guide-text guide-text--lg">
        A CSR tells the certificate authority what domain(s) to include in the certificate. You have two options:
      </p>

      <div class="options-grid">
        <div class="card card--compact">
          <h3 class="card-title">In-browser generator</h3>
          <p class="card-description">
            The dashboard includes a CSR generator that uses the WebCrypto API.
            Your private key is generated in your browser and <strong>never leaves your device</strong>.
            Fill in the form, click generate, and the CSR is ready to submit.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card card--compact">
          <h3 class="card-title">OpenSSL (CLI)</h3>
          <p class="card-description guide-text">
            Generate a CSR with OpenSSL on your own machine:
          </p>
          <div class="code-block code-block--flush">
            <pre><code>openssl req -new -newkey rsa:2048 \
  -nodes -keyout key.pem \
  -out csr.pem \
  -subj "/CN=example.com"</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 6 -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <div class="step-marker">
        <div class="step-number">6</div>
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Submit CSR and download your certificate</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="guide-text">
        Paste your CSR PEM in the dashboard and click <strong>Submit</strong>, or use the API:
      </p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><code set:html={`<span class="code-comment"># Submit CSR</span>
curl -X POST https://api.krakenkey.io/certs/tls \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\
  -d '{"csrPem": "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE REQUEST-----\\n...\\n-----END CERTIFICATE REQUEST-----"}'`} /></pre>
      </div>
      <p class="guide-text">
        KrakenKey creates a DNS-01 challenge record, Let's Encrypt validates it, and your certificate is issued &mdash; typically in about <strong class="text-accent">4 minutes</strong>.
      </p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><code><span class="code-comment"># Check status and download</span>
curl https://api.krakenkey.io/certs/tls/<span class="code-muted">CERT_ID</span> \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN"</code></pre>
      </div>
      <p class="text-muted">
        When <code>status</code> is <code>"issued"</code>, the response includes your signed certificate PEM. Download it from the dashboard or copy it from the API response.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- API Key section -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2 class="guide-heading">Using an API key</h2>
      <p class="guide-text">
        For programmatic access, generate an API key from the dashboard under your profile. API keys use the same <code>Authorization: Bearer</code> header as session tokens:
      </p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><code><span class="code-comment"># Generate an API key from the dashboard, then:</span>
curl https://api.krakenkey.io/certs/tls \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer kk_your_api_key_here"</code></pre>
      </div>
      <p class="text-muted">
        See the <a href="/docs/api" class="link">API Reference</a> for the full endpoint documentation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- What's next -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2 class="guide-heading">What's next</h2>
      <ul class="next-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Add more domains</strong> &mdash; repeat steps 2&ndash;4 for each domain you want to issue certificates for
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Automate with the API</strong> &mdash; integrate certificate issuance into your deployment pipeline using the <a href="/docs/api" class="link">REST API</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Wildcard certificates</strong> &mdash; submit a CSR with <code>*.example.com</code> as the common name (DNS-01 supports wildcards)
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTA />
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .guide {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .guide-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .guide-section:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .guide-text {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .guide-text--lg {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .guide-note {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .step-marker {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .step-number {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-info-surface);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .guide-heading {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .guide-subheading {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .guide-subheading--spaced {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .prereq-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .prereq-list li {
    padding: 0.375rem 0;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .prereq-list li::before {
    content: '\2713';
    color: var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .code-block {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-md) 1.25rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .code-block--flush {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .code-block pre {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .code-block code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .code-comment {
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .code-string {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .code-muted {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .dns-table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }

  .dns-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  .dns-table th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.75rem var(--space-md);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .dns-table td {
    padding: 0.75rem var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-text);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .dns-table code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .options-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .link {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .link:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-hover);
  }

  .next-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .next-list li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .next-list li::before {
    content: '\2192';
    color: var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .options-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .dns-table td,
    .dns-table th {
      padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .step-marker {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
